WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:14.670 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm Dr. Theresa Bullard,
and this is Mystery Teachings.

00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.240 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.240 --> 00:00:24.230 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible to travel
beyond our physical body

00:00:24.230 --> 00:00:26.990 align:middle line:84%
while we're still
alive here on Earth?

00:00:26.990 --> 00:00:29.720 align:middle line:10%
Is this something we can
learn to do consciously?

00:00:29.720 --> 00:00:34.250 align:middle line:84%
And if so, what mysteries
might it reveal to us?

00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:37.460 align:middle line:84%
Astral travel is defined
as the art and science

00:00:37.460 --> 00:00:41.780 align:middle line:84%
of expanding our consciousness
to travel beyond the body,

00:00:41.780 --> 00:00:44.150 align:middle line:90%
and often to the stars.

00:00:44.150 --> 00:00:46.970 align:middle line:84%
We have this ability
to do this because we

00:00:46.970 --> 00:00:49.370 align:middle line:90%
are infinite spiritual beings.

00:00:49.370 --> 00:00:52.320 align:middle line:90%
We are multidimensional beings.

00:00:52.320 --> 00:00:55.500 align:middle line:84%
Astral travel is a natural
part of our experience

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:58.620 align:middle line:84%
as spiritual beings operating
this vehicle that we

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:00.600 align:middle line:90%
call a physical body.

00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:05.110 align:middle line:84%
We all astral travel naturally,
but most of the time,

00:01:05.110 --> 00:01:07.260 align:middle line:90%
we aren't conscious of it.

00:01:07.260 --> 00:01:09.030 align:middle line:84%
Let me share with
you a personal story

00:01:09.030 --> 00:01:12.330 align:middle line:84%
about some of my early
encounters with astral travel.

00:01:12.330 --> 00:01:14.790 align:middle line:84%
I learned about some of
my earliest experiences

00:01:14.790 --> 00:01:17.550 align:middle line:84%
with it from stories that my
mom shared with me that I really

00:01:17.550 --> 00:01:19.620 align:middle line:90%
had no conscious memory of.

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:23.220 align:middle line:84%
But apparently, when I was
just a three-month-old baby,

00:01:23.220 --> 00:01:26.730 align:middle line:84%
my mom had several waking
dreams where she'd look up

00:01:26.730 --> 00:01:30.310 align:middle line:84%
and she'd see that I was flying
in circles over their bed.

00:01:30.310 --> 00:01:32.700 align:middle line:84%
She'd tell me come back
down, but I was just

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:34.660 align:middle line:90%
having too much fun.

00:01:34.660 --> 00:01:38.010 align:middle line:84%
And according to her, this
became a nightly routine.

00:01:38.010 --> 00:01:40.620 align:middle line:84%
Then there was one
night where she

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:43.830 align:middle line:84%
heard me crying by
the bed in her dream,

00:01:43.830 --> 00:01:45.880 align:middle line:84%
and she kept trying
to pick me up.

00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:49.680 align:middle line:84%
And when she finally did,
apparently my head came off.

00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:51.630 align:middle line:84%
Needless to say, my
mom thought she was

00:01:51.630 --> 00:01:54.280 align:middle line:90%
going to die of a heart attack.

00:01:54.280 --> 00:01:57.440 align:middle line:84%
And when she startled awake,
I wasn't there, of course.

00:01:57.440 --> 00:02:00.120 align:middle line:84%
But then a few minutes later,
she did hear me crying,

00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:04.100 align:middle line:84%
so she jumped up out of
bed and ran into my room.

00:02:04.100 --> 00:02:07.500 align:middle line:84%
And when she saw that I was
OK and just wanted to be fed,

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:11.250 align:middle line:84%
she said to me, OK,
Theresa, that's enough.

00:02:11.250 --> 00:02:13.620 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
scare me to death.

00:02:13.620 --> 00:02:16.830 align:middle line:84%
Don't you ever do
that to me again.

00:02:16.830 --> 00:02:20.490 align:middle line:84%
Now at that point, she says
I looked at her with a smile,

00:02:20.490 --> 00:02:23.880 align:middle line:84%
and I gave her a wink at
just three months old.

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:26.070 align:middle line:84%
And then she never
saw me do it again.

00:02:26.070 --> 00:02:30.660 align:middle line:90%


00:02:30.660 --> 00:02:34.230 align:middle line:84%
Now, I've always had a very
active and vivid dreamtime,

00:02:34.230 --> 00:02:37.770 align:middle line:84%
and much of it felt
very real, but it

00:02:37.770 --> 00:02:41.100 align:middle line:84%
wasn't until I was an adult
that I consciously started

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:43.860 align:middle line:90%
to try astral travel again.

00:02:43.860 --> 00:02:47.340 align:middle line:84%
What's interesting is
that, as an adult, when

00:02:47.340 --> 00:02:50.370 align:middle line:84%
I started to explore with
it, I really struggled.

00:02:50.370 --> 00:02:52.890 align:middle line:84%
I had a hard time,
because I had this sense

00:02:52.890 --> 00:02:55.170 align:middle line:90%
of needing to be in control.

00:02:55.170 --> 00:02:57.810 align:middle line:84%
And not surprisingly,
it was my mom

00:02:57.810 --> 00:03:02.130 align:middle line:84%
who brought astral travel
back into my life as an adult.

00:03:02.130 --> 00:03:04.020 align:middle line:84%
She was very involved
with the Monroe

00:03:04.020 --> 00:03:06.720 align:middle line:84%
Institute, a group of
consciousness explorers

00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:10.950 align:middle line:84%
who specialize in techniques
for journeying out of body.

00:03:10.950 --> 00:03:14.250 align:middle line:84%
The Monroe Institute uses
technologies like binaural beat

00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:16.140 align:middle line:84%
brainwave entrainment,
and various

00:03:16.140 --> 00:03:19.080 align:middle line:84%
visualizations to shift
into an altered state

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:21.660 align:middle line:90%
for astral travel.

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:25.470 align:middle line:84%
During my first time at their
week-long gateway program,

00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:29.070 align:middle line:84%
they taught us several
different visualizations to try.

00:03:29.070 --> 00:03:33.000 align:middle line:84%
We'd lay down, and we'd imagined
floating up out of body,

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:35.730 align:middle line:84%
or sitting up and
moving out that way.

00:03:35.730 --> 00:03:38.515 align:middle line:84%
We could barrel roll out, or we
could use the rake technique,

00:03:38.515 --> 00:03:40.890 align:middle line:84%
where it's like someone's
stepping on a rake at your feet

00:03:40.890 --> 00:03:42.420 align:middle line:90%
and you pop out.

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:44.940 align:middle line:84%
We had all these
different techniques,

00:03:44.940 --> 00:03:47.310 align:middle line:84%
and we were instructed
to try all of them

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:50.130 align:middle line:90%
to find what works for us.

00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:52.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, as I was trying
these different methods,

00:03:52.920 --> 00:03:56.160 align:middle line:84%
I noticed that every time I
started to feel that shift out

00:03:56.160 --> 00:03:59.850 align:middle line:84%
of body, one of two things
would happen for me.

00:03:59.850 --> 00:04:03.700 align:middle line:84%
Either my mind would kick in, I
would say, oh, it's happening,

00:04:03.700 --> 00:04:06.390 align:middle line:84%
and then that would
slam me back in again,

00:04:06.390 --> 00:04:10.710 align:middle line:84%
or I would feel disoriented,
and I'd snap back into my body

00:04:10.710 --> 00:04:13.470 align:middle line:90%
because I didn't feel safe.

00:04:13.470 --> 00:04:16.410 align:middle line:84%
In the end, it was a
great week of training,

00:04:16.410 --> 00:04:18.060 align:middle line:84%
but the way I ended
up doing it was

00:04:18.060 --> 00:04:21.660 align:middle line:84%
to just sit up and project my
consciousness into a journey

00:04:21.660 --> 00:04:26.010 align:middle line:84%
while still maintaining
awareness of being in my body.

00:04:26.010 --> 00:04:28.410 align:middle line:84%
When I then later came to
the Modern Mystery School's

00:04:28.410 --> 00:04:30.750 align:middle line:84%
training on astral travel,
I found a technique

00:04:30.750 --> 00:04:35.393 align:middle line:84%
that really worked reliably
for me and felt really safe.

00:04:35.393 --> 00:04:36.810 align:middle line:84%
The method from
the Mystery School

00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:39.990 align:middle line:84%
gave me a reliable tool
to confidently astral

00:04:39.990 --> 00:04:43.260 align:middle line:84%
travel, which is why I am
thrilled to be able to share it

00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:46.350 align:middle line:90%
with you today.

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:48.430 align:middle line:84%
And before we get
into that, though,

00:04:48.430 --> 00:04:53.410 align:middle line:84%
let's get clear on the dos and
don'ts, as well as address some

00:04:53.410 --> 00:04:56.350 align:middle line:84%
of the myths about
astral travel.

00:04:56.350 --> 00:04:58.510 align:middle line:84%
And even more
important is that we

00:04:58.510 --> 00:05:01.420 align:middle line:84%
need to get a better
understanding of why

00:05:01.420 --> 00:05:04.720 align:middle line:84%
we would astral travel
in the first place.

00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:08.760 align:middle line:84%
There is a whole purpose,
an art, to astral travel.

00:05:08.760 --> 00:05:12.110 align:middle line:84%
Now this brings up an
important question.

00:05:12.110 --> 00:05:15.610 align:middle line:84%
What is the purpose
of astral travel?

00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:17.890 align:middle line:84%
Astral travel is
an art form that

00:05:17.890 --> 00:05:22.420 align:middle line:84%
is about moving beyond our
normal everyday reality.

00:05:22.420 --> 00:05:24.940 align:middle line:84%
Our ultimate purpose
for astral travel

00:05:24.940 --> 00:05:29.620 align:middle line:84%
is to progress toward our
full potential and divinity.

00:05:29.620 --> 00:05:32.050 align:middle line:90%
How does it help us do that?

00:05:32.050 --> 00:05:35.560 align:middle line:84%
With astral travel, we
open up our perception

00:05:35.560 --> 00:05:37.990 align:middle line:90%
of our multidimensionality.

00:05:37.990 --> 00:05:40.450 align:middle line:84%
We learn about ourselves
and our purpose,

00:05:40.450 --> 00:05:42.820 align:middle line:84%
and we can take what
we learn from it

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:46.480 align:middle line:84%
and then put it into
service in this world.

00:05:46.480 --> 00:05:49.690 align:middle line:84%
Some people want to use
astral travel to explore,

00:05:49.690 --> 00:05:52.210 align:middle line:90%
and others are simply curious.

00:05:52.210 --> 00:05:54.880 align:middle line:84%
Others may doubt
it's even possible,

00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:58.640 align:middle line:84%
and want to see if it's
something they can actually do.

00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:02.050 align:middle line:84%
And some people have a sense
that they're already doing it

00:06:02.050 --> 00:06:03.910 align:middle line:84%
in their dreams, and
they want to learn

00:06:03.910 --> 00:06:07.240 align:middle line:90%
how to do it consciously.

00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:10.390 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the reason may
be, my word of advice

00:06:10.390 --> 00:06:13.910 align:middle line:84%
is that astral travel is
not to be used lightly.

00:06:13.910 --> 00:06:16.900 align:middle line:84%
It's not about becoming a
tourist on the astral plane,

00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:21.820 align:middle line:84%
and is definitely not to be
used for any sort of ill intent.

00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:23.410 align:middle line:84%
If you can believe
it, we've actually

00:06:23.410 --> 00:06:26.530 align:middle line:84%
had people inquire to
learn astral travel from us

00:06:26.530 --> 00:06:29.350 align:middle line:84%
so that they could spy on a
boyfriend or girlfriend who

00:06:29.350 --> 00:06:30.940 align:middle line:90%
they thought was cheating.

00:06:30.940 --> 00:06:36.020 align:middle line:84%
It's definitely not
to be used for that.

00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:37.960 align:middle line:90%
Think about this.

00:06:37.960 --> 00:06:40.180 align:middle line:84%
How would you change
your life if you

00:06:40.180 --> 00:06:44.350 align:middle line:84%
knew that everything you
thought, said, and did

00:06:44.350 --> 00:06:46.180 align:middle line:90%
was being recorded?

00:06:46.180 --> 00:06:47.950 align:middle line:90%
Well, guess what?

00:06:47.950 --> 00:06:49.310 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:06:49.310 --> 00:06:50.890 align:middle line:90%
And who's recording it?

00:06:50.890 --> 00:06:54.790 align:middle line:84%
You are, but you're recording
it from the perspective

00:06:54.790 --> 00:06:58.670 align:middle line:84%
of your higher self rather
than the personality.

00:06:58.670 --> 00:07:01.450 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the ways
we can use astral travel

00:07:01.450 --> 00:07:04.780 align:middle line:84%
is to consciously
review those records.

00:07:04.780 --> 00:07:07.960 align:middle line:84%
We can become more aware of
our higher self's perspective

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:10.810 align:middle line:90%
on how we're living our life.

00:07:10.810 --> 00:07:13.300 align:middle line:84%
And with that
perspective, we can

00:07:13.300 --> 00:07:16.540 align:middle line:84%
see where we might want to
make adjustments to be more

00:07:16.540 --> 00:07:19.390 align:middle line:84%
on track, and live
life in greater

00:07:19.390 --> 00:07:22.330 align:middle line:90%
alignment with our higher self.

00:07:22.330 --> 00:07:25.270 align:middle line:84%
How exactly does
this happen well,

00:07:25.270 --> 00:07:28.540 align:middle line:84%
you may not have realized
it, but you're already very

00:07:28.540 --> 00:07:31.000 align:middle line:90%
experienced with astral travel.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:33.620 align:middle line:90%
Many people aren't aware of it.

00:07:33.620 --> 00:07:36.730 align:middle line:84%
Many people don't even think
that they dream at night.

00:07:36.730 --> 00:07:39.580 align:middle line:84%
But I can assure you
everyone does it,

00:07:39.580 --> 00:07:43.300 align:middle line:90%
whether we remember it or not.

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:47.320 align:middle line:84%
This means we already have
this ability innate within us.

00:07:47.320 --> 00:07:50.410 align:middle line:84%
We just need to remember
it and become conscious

00:07:50.410 --> 00:07:52.330 align:middle line:84%
of the process of
actually doing it.

00:07:52.330 --> 00:07:54.840 align:middle line:90%


00:07:54.840 --> 00:07:58.210 align:middle line:84%
Let's go back to that recording
of our thoughts, words,

00:07:58.210 --> 00:07:59.010 align:middle line:90%
and deeds.

00:07:59.010 --> 00:08:01.170 align:middle line:90%
How does this work?

00:08:01.170 --> 00:08:04.920 align:middle line:84%
Well, every night when we
sleep, as we go into the deepest

00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:07.530 align:middle line:84%
parts of our sleep
cycle, we reach

00:08:07.530 --> 00:08:12.240 align:middle line:84%
a very slow delta brainwave
state of less than 3 Hertz.

00:08:12.240 --> 00:08:14.700 align:middle line:90%
It's a dreamless sleep.

00:08:14.700 --> 00:08:16.980 align:middle line:84%
And when we're in this
state, our higher self

00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:21.540 align:middle line:84%
guides us up out of our body,
up through a tunnel of light,

00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:25.710 align:middle line:84%
and we travel into the higher
spiritual plains, all the way

00:08:25.710 --> 00:08:29.240 align:middle line:84%
up to what's called
the Akashic Zone.

00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:32.809 align:middle line:84%
And there, we record
everything that we thought,

00:08:32.809 --> 00:08:35.929 align:middle line:90%
said, and did that day.

00:08:35.929 --> 00:08:39.590 align:middle line:84%
This is something everyone
does without exception.

00:08:39.590 --> 00:08:42.570 align:middle line:90%


00:08:42.570 --> 00:08:45.730 align:middle line:90%
What, exactly, is astral travel?

00:08:45.730 --> 00:08:49.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, the word astral is derived
from the Greek word astron,

00:08:49.830 --> 00:08:51.750 align:middle line:90%
meaning star.

00:08:51.750 --> 00:08:53.910 align:middle line:84%
The word was originally
used by the Greeks

00:08:53.910 --> 00:08:56.670 align:middle line:84%
to describe the
home of the gods.

00:08:56.670 --> 00:09:00.390 align:middle line:84%
These gods lived among the
stars such as Mars and Venus,

00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:03.240 align:middle line:90%
Jupiter, and the constellations.

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:05.490 align:middle line:84%
The art and science
of astral travel

00:09:05.490 --> 00:09:07.710 align:middle line:84%
is learning how to
consciously shift

00:09:07.710 --> 00:09:11.780 align:middle line:84%
what's called our assemblage
point beyond our body.

00:09:11.780 --> 00:09:13.950 align:middle line:84%
The assemblage point
is the vantage point

00:09:13.950 --> 00:09:16.860 align:middle line:84%
from where we
perceive and assemble

00:09:16.860 --> 00:09:20.610 align:middle line:84%
our view of the
universe around us.

00:09:20.610 --> 00:09:23.310 align:middle line:84%
Although astral travel is
often depicted as though we're

00:09:23.310 --> 00:09:27.130 align:middle line:84%
leaving the body behind, we
don't actually leave the body

00:09:27.130 --> 00:09:28.980 align:middle line:90%
when we astral travel.

00:09:28.980 --> 00:09:32.940 align:middle line:84%
I say that because our
spirit is infinite.

00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:35.910 align:middle line:84%
So we're simply
shifting our perspective

00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:40.140 align:middle line:84%
to another point within
our infinite spirit.

00:09:40.140 --> 00:09:41.940 align:middle line:84%
We're moving the
assemblage point

00:09:41.940 --> 00:09:45.360 align:middle line:84%
from point A, which tends
to be here in the body,

00:09:45.360 --> 00:09:48.210 align:middle line:84%
usually around the
head, to point B,

00:09:48.210 --> 00:09:51.090 align:middle line:90%
wherever we decide that to be.

00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:53.640 align:middle line:84%
Surprisingly, one of
the biggest challenges

00:09:53.640 --> 00:09:56.730 align:middle line:84%
is that we're actually
always astral traveling.

00:09:56.730 --> 00:10:01.080 align:middle line:84%
It's not just when we're asleep
or trying to do it consciously.

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:03.540 align:middle line:84%
We're astral traveling
throughout our day.

00:10:03.540 --> 00:10:06.000 align:middle line:84%
In fact, our astral
travel experience

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:11.800 align:middle line:84%
can be so real that we may have
trouble making the distinction.

00:10:11.800 --> 00:10:15.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, what I mean is that we're
always traveling in the mind.

00:10:15.610 --> 00:10:19.540 align:middle line:84%
So where is our
mind traveling to?

00:10:19.540 --> 00:10:21.160 align:middle line:90%
Is it in the past?

00:10:21.160 --> 00:10:22.220 align:middle line:90%
The future?

00:10:22.220 --> 00:10:23.680 align:middle line:90%
The now?

00:10:23.680 --> 00:10:25.210 align:middle line:90%
Are we daydreaming?

00:10:25.210 --> 00:10:27.420 align:middle line:84%
Are we living in
a fantasy world?

00:10:27.420 --> 00:10:31.290 align:middle line:84%
Or are we present
in the here and now?

00:10:31.290 --> 00:10:33.780 align:middle line:84%
If you're not in
the here and now,

00:10:33.780 --> 00:10:36.870 align:middle line:84%
truly present with
what's in front of you,

00:10:36.870 --> 00:10:39.090 align:middle line:90%
then where are you?

00:10:39.090 --> 00:10:42.900 align:middle line:84%
And for that matter,
are we really even here,

00:10:42.900 --> 00:10:45.180 align:middle line:90%
in this physical life on Earth?

00:10:45.180 --> 00:10:49.110 align:middle line:84%
Or is this just a projection
from the hologram?

00:10:49.110 --> 00:10:52.500 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps we're really at
the Great Central Sun,

00:10:52.500 --> 00:10:55.260 align:middle line:84%
and our assemblage point
is just projected here

00:10:55.260 --> 00:10:57.510 align:middle line:90%
into this density level.

00:10:57.510 --> 00:11:01.340 align:middle line:84%
That's a concept we
discussed in season one.

00:11:01.340 --> 00:11:05.300 align:middle line:84%
Some mystery teachings say that
we're always astral traveling,

00:11:05.300 --> 00:11:08.810 align:middle line:84%
except for when we're
in the here and now,

00:11:08.810 --> 00:11:12.110 align:middle line:84%
fully connected to our
divinity and fully conscious

00:11:12.110 --> 00:11:15.050 align:middle line:90%
of ourselves.

00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:21.240 align:middle line:84%
So how do we get our awareness
fully into the here and now?

